						<summary>

						<p>Naṭarāja temple, Slab built into the floor in front of the Gaṇapati shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• Manmatha [Dhanus ?].</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in late characters is carelessly inscribed and unfinished.</p>						

						<p>On top are the figures of the Sun and moon with a Śivaliṅgam and Nandi below.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the bathing <hi rend="italic">(tirumañjanam)</hi> of God Chidambarēśvarar and a benefaction for a service connected with this ceremony. One Nāgama-nāyakkar is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
